### BIOS/UEFI Session 1 — Navigation and Identification
Date: 30 March 2026
Tool: Lenovo BIOS Simulator (ThinkPad X12 Detachable Gen 1)

#### Tasks Completed
- Navigated the UEFI BIOS interface using keyboard-only controls
- Identified `System-unit serial number` and `UEFI BIOS Version`
- Verified `System Date` and `System Time` accuracy
- Investigated `Wake On LAN` settings in the Config menu
- Analysed the `Boot Priority Order` list

#### Key Concepts
- `Serial Number`: Unique hardware ID used for tracking and support
- `WOL (Wake On LAN)`: Enabling remote power-on for maintenance
- `PXE Boot`: Booting from a network server to install operating systems
- `Windows Boot Manager`: The primary boot entry for modern Windows OS

#### Lessons Learned
- Synchronised time is critical for secure handshakes between the hardware and OS services like Entra ID
- PXE booting is the standard for "imaging" multiple machines in an enterprise environment like GTS
- Navigating BIOS requires understanding keyboard shortcuts (F5/F6 to move items, Arrows to navigate)

